Ques: What is virtual DOM ?
Ans: The Virtual DOM is a lightweight in-memory representation of the real DOM elements. React uses it to update the UI efficiently by calculating the difference (diffing) between
the previous and the new virtual DOM and updating only the parts of the real DOM tha have changed.

Ques: Explain the difference between state and props.
Ans: Props: Passed from parent to child components, read-only, and cannot be modified by the receiving component.
     State: Managed within a component, mutable, and used to store information that can change over time.

Ques: What are controlled components?
Answer: Controlled components are form elements (inputs, selects, etc.) where React manages the value. The component’s state holds the form value, and every input change is handled by an event handler.

Ques: How does React handle reconcilation ?
Ans: React uses a reconciliation algorithm to efficiently update the DOM. It compares the new virtual DOM with the previous one, calculates the minimum number of updates, and 
batches changes to the real DOM.

